{
  "_comment": [
    "Benchmark sweep configuration for the ExaMiniMD Molecular Dynamics proxy app.",
    "Each scenario maps to one BenchmarkScenario object in metrics_collector.py.",
    "",
    "Application: ExaMiniMD (ECP proxy for molecular dynamics codes)",
    "Executable:  ExaMiniMD",
    "Input file:  LAMMPS-format .lj file passed via -il flag",
    "",
    "CLI argument format:",
    "  -il <input_file>          LAMMPS-format input file",
    "  --comm-type MPI           Use MPI communication (Serial for single-rank)",
    "  --kokkos-threads=N        Number of Kokkos threads per MPI rank",
    "",
    "Design:",
    "  - Fixed 4 MPI processes for all scenarios.",
    "  - 3 workload sizes controlled by the 'run N' directive in the input file:",
    "      short  : run 50   (50 timesteps)",
    "      medium : run 100  (100 timesteps, default)",
    "      long   : run 200  (200 timesteps)",
    "  - The run_examinimd_validation.sh script generates three input files:",
    "      ${INPUT_DIR}/in.lj.short   (run 50)",
    "      ${INPUT_DIR}/in.lj.medium  (run 100)",
    "      ${INPUT_DIR}/in.lj.long    (run 200)",
    "    where INPUT_DIR defaults to tests/ecp/vanillas/ExaMiniMD/input.",
    "  - For each workload: 1 failure-free baseline + 5 failure scenarios",
    "    with injection delays of 10s, 20s, 40s, 80s, and 160s.",
    "  - Total: 3 × (1 + 5) = 18 scenarios.",
    "",
    "Set INPUT_DIR env var to override the directory containing the input files.",
    "Default: tests/ecp/vanillas/ExaMiniMD/input",
    "(resolved via INPUT_DIR env var in run_examinimd_validation.sh)"
  ],
  "scenarios": [
